  "companies": {
    "observationHtml": "<li><strong>Palo Alto Networks</strong> leads all non-Google companies with <strong>14</strong> sessions — a persistent presence throughout the program.</li><li>The major consulting firms (Accenture, McKinsey & Company, Deloitte, PwC, Cognizant, HCLTech) add up to <strong>36 sessions combined</strong> — more than any individual non-Google company. A big slice of the conference is about enterprise adoption, with consultants as the delivery vehicle.</li><li><strong>NVIDIA</strong> at #8 (9 sessions) makes the AI hardware dependency explicit — the software story at this conference runs on their chips.</li><li><strong>Anthropic</strong> appears 8 times — Google's AI model investment earns a recurring stage presence.</li><li><strong>Shopify</strong> (13) and <strong>Snap</strong> (5) are consumer brands, not enterprise software companies — Google is using them as scale proof points for what Cloud infrastructure can handle.</li>",
